title: The House Bunny

title: iCarly Revival

title: Saving Silverman

title: F Troop

description: It centers around an egomaniacal supervillain with a really big head and a really little body, who struggles to maintain control of his evil organization and his demanding family.

title: Harold & Kumar Go to White Castle

title: Garden State

title: Paddington

title: The Librarians

title: Gregory's Girl
description: Gregory is a normal teen who is infatuated with a classmate. He must work to win her affection.

title: Crashing
description: A comedy series following the lives of six 20- and 30-somethings living together as property guardians of a large, disused hospital.

title: The Iron Giant
description: A young boy befriends a giant robot from outer space that a paranoid government agent wants to destroy.

title: Body of Proof

title: The Nutty Professor

title: Hocus Pocus

title: Get Shorty
description: The adventures of a mobster-turned-movie producer in Hollywood. TV show based on Elmore Leonard's novel and subsequent film.

title: The Switch

title: Mallrats

title: Party Down

title: Howard the Duck
description: A sarcastic humanoid duck is pulled from his homeworld to Earth where he must stop an alien invasion with the help of a nerdy scientist and a struggling female rock singer.

title: A Fish Called Wanda

title: Rescue Me

title: The Bad News Bears
description: An aging, down-on-his-luck ex-minor leaguer coaches a team of misfits in an ultra-competitive California little league.

title: P.S. I Love You

title: Isn't It Romantic

title: Hackers

description: Tim Avery, an aspiring cartoonist, finds himself in a predicament when his dog stumbles upon the mask of Loki. Then after conceiving an infant son "born of the mask", he discovers just how looney child raising can be.

title: Signed, Sealed, Delivered
description: A group of postal detectives work to solve the mysteries behind undeliverable letters and packages from the past, delivering them when they are needed most.

title: I Dream of Jeannie
description: A United States astronaut finds his life vastly complicated when he stumbles on to a bottle containing a female genie.

title: Raising Arizona
description: When a childless couple of an ex-con and an ex-cop decide to help themselves to one of another family's quintuplets, their lives become more complicated than they anticipated.

title: The Art of Self-Defense

title: Awkward.

title: EverAfter
description: The Brothers Grimm arrive at the home of a wealthy Grande Dame who speaks of the many legends surrounding the fable of the cinder girl before telling the "true" story of her ancestor.

title: The Good Dinosaur

title: To Wong Foo Thanks for Everything, Julie Newmar

description: The fourth and final chapter of the 'Hotel Transylvania' franchise.

title: Where the Heart Is
description: A pregnant seventeen-year-old rebuilds her life after being abandoned by her boyfriend at a Walmart in Sequoyah, Oklahoma.

title: St. Elsewhere

title: Transparent
description: An L.A. family with serious boundary issues have their past and future unravel when a dramatic admission causes everyone's secrets to spill out.

description: The life of a twelve-year-old boy who happens to be a blue cat as he lives with his family and other strange creatures.

title: Father of the Bride

title: Pan

title: Fired Up!
description: The two most popular guys in high school decide to ditch football camp for cheerleader camp. For the girls and for the glory.

title: Miranda
description: Socially inept Miranda always gets into awkward situations; working in her joke shop with best friend Stevie, being hounded by her pushy mother, and around her crush Gary.

As the pair drive 2,000 head of cattle over unforgiving landscape, they experience the bombing of Darwin, Australia, by Japanese forces firsthand.

title: Step by Step
description: Two families become one, step by step.

title: Heartbreakers
description: A mother and daughter con team seduce and scam wealthy men.

title: Coach

description: The Cotswolds-based PR guru turned amateur sleuth returns for a series of comedic murder-mysteries based on the books by M.C. Beaton.

description: Sir Sidney Ruff-Diamond looks after the British outpost near the Khyber Pass. Protected by the kilted Third Foot and Mouth regiment, you would think they were safe but the Khazi of Kalabar has other ideas.

description: The Kadam family leaves India for France where they open a restaurant directly across the road from Madame Mallory's Michelin-starred eatery.

title: Me, Myself & Irene
description: A nice-guy cop with Dissociative Identity Disorder must protect a woman on the run from a corrupt ex-boyfriend and his associates.

title: Warm Bodies
description: After a highly unusual zombie saves a still-living girl from an attack, the two form a relationship that sets in motion events that might transform the entire lifeless world.

title: Sister, Sister

title: Encanto
description: A young Colombian girl has to face the frustration of being the only member of her family without magical powers.

title: Smokey and the Bandit
description: The Bandit is hired on to run a tractor-trailer full of beer over state lines, in hot pursuit by a pesky sheriff.

title: Short Circuit
description: Number 5 of a group of experimental robots in a lab is electrocuted, suddenly becomes intelligent, and escapes.

title: National Lampoon's Christmas Vacation
description: The Griswold family's plans for a big family Christmas predictably turn into a big disaster.

title: Crocodile Dundee
description: An American reporter goes to the Australian outback to meet an eccentric crocodile poacher and invites him to New York City.

title: The Book of Life
description: Manolo, a young man who is torn between fulfilling the expectations of his family and following his heart, embarks on an adventure that spans three fantastic worlds where he must face his greatest fears.

description: Venice: A city full of beauty, love, music, and brutal trash talk. Join the Pom's team in saying "Au Revoir, Chris Hemsworth".

description: Follows Bow's parents, Paul and Alicia, who are forced to move from a hippie commune to the suburbs to better provide for their family after the dissolution of their cult.

description: Miranda runs a boot camp for the recently brokenhearted. She begins to form a connection with new client Ben who is also a reporter, investigating whether her boot camp is a scam or a phenomenon.

title: Kajillionaire
description: A woman's life is turned upside down when her criminal parents invite an outsider to join them on a major heist they're planning.

title: Designing Women
description: The misadventures of four women and their handyman running a design firm in Atlanta, Georgia.

title: The Big Year
description: Two bird enthusiasts try to defeat the cocky, cutthroat world record holder in a year-long bird-spotting competition.

description: The Mystery Inc. gang must save Coolsville from an attack of their past monsters brought to life by an evil masked figure trying to take down the gang.

title: Kung Fury 2
description: The story will focus on Kung Fury's universe with no real connection to the short movie other than the lead character.

title: Popstar: Never Stop Never Stopping
description: When it becomes clear that his solo album is a failure, a former boy band member does everything in his power to maintain his celebrity status.

title: American Pie 2
description: Jim and his friends are now in college, and they decide to meet up at the beach house for some fun.

title: The Comeback Trail
description: Two movie producers who owe money to the mob set up their aging movie star for an insurance scam to try and save themselves. But they wind up getting more than they ever imagined.

title: The Farewell
description: A Chinese family discovers their grandmother has only a short while left to live and decide to keep her in the dark, scheduling a wedding to gather before she dies.

title: Kaguya-sama wa kokurasetai ~ Tensai tachi no ren'ai zunô sen ~
description: The proudly privileged top two students of an elite school each makes it their mission to be the first to extract a confession of love from the other.

title: Nathan for You
description: Nathan Fielder uses his business degree and life experiences to help real small businesses turn a profit. But because of his unorthodox approach, Nathan's genuine efforts to do good often draw real people into an experience far beyond what they signed up for.

title: Kung fu
description: In Shanghai, China in the 1940s, a wannabe gangster aspires to join the notorious "Axe Gang" while residents of a housing complex exhibit extraordinary powers in defending their turf.

title: Jonathan Creek
description: Working from his home in a converted windmill, Jonathan Creek is a magician with a natural ability for solving puzzles. He soon puts this ability to the use of solving impossible crimes and mysterious murders.

title: The Addams Family
description: The misadventures of a blissfully macabre but extremely loving family.

title: Kim Possible
description: Heroes Kim and Ron face the problems of starting high school as freshmen when their team gets an addition. Every hero needs a villain and one's just been sprung from prison. Will Kim save the world again or will high school bog her down?

title: Swiss Army Man
description: A hopeless man stranded on a deserted island befriends a dead body, and together they go on a surreal journey to get home.

title: Blast from the Past
description: A naive man comes out into the world after spending 35 years in a nuclear fallout shelter.

title: The Brothers Grimm
description: Will and Jake Grimm are traveling con-artists who encounter a genuine fairy-tale curse which requires true courage instead of their usual bogus exorcisms.

title: Still Game

title: Killers
description: A vacationing woman meets her ideal man, leading to a swift marriage. Back at home, however, their idyllic life is upset when they discover their neighbors could be assassins who have been contracted to kill the couple.

title: You Don't Mess with the Zohan
description: An Israeli Special Forces Soldier fakes his death so he can re-emerge in New York City as a hair stylist.

title: Yeoshingangrim
description: After being bullied and discriminated because of her ugly looks, a high school girl transforms herself into a gorgeous "goddess" and quickly rises to fame after mastering the art of makeup via online tutorial videos.

title: Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs
description: A local scientist is often regarded as a failure until he invents a machine that can make food fall from the sky. But little does he know, that things are about to take a turn for the worst.

title: Naked

title: Practical Magic
description: Two witch sisters, raised by their eccentric aunts in a small town, face closed-minded prejudice and a curse which threatens to prevent them ever finding lasting love.

title: About a Boy

title: PAW Patrol

title: Philomena

title: We Broke Up

title: Two Night Stand

title: Blue Mountain State

title: Vampire Academy
description: Rose Hathaway is a Dhampir, half human-half vampire, a guardian of the Moroi, peaceful, mortal vampires living discreetly within our world. Her calling is to protect the Moroi from bloodthirsty, immortal Vampires, the Strigoi.

title: A Good Year

title: Raven's Home

title: George Lopez

title: Lars and the Real Girl
description: A delusional young man strikes up an unconventional relationship with a doll he finds on the Internet.

title: Gake no ue no Ponyo
description: A five-year-old boy develops a relationship with Ponyo, a young goldfish princess who longs to become a human after falling in love with him.

title: Red Oaks
description: A coming-of-age comedy set in the "go-go" 80s about a college student enjoying a last hurrah before summer comes to an end--and the future begins.

title: What Women Want

title: Last Christmas

A high school teacher travels back in time to prevent John F. Kennedy's assassination.
